{"title": "Minor Issues: How can an English-speaking household help kids with second language?", "tags": "singapore", "timestamp": "2023-11-26", "content": "SINGAPORE \u2013 My resolution for 2024 is to have more elements of spoken Mandarin around the home. The reason is simple: My youngest daughter, who will be in Secondary 3 next year, failed her Sec 2 Chinese examinations.\nPart of the reason was that she decided to stop Chinese tuition in the middle of the year. \u201cI\u2019ll study on my own,\u201d she declared."}